          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- MY EXPERIENCE: BEFORE/AFTER CASE STUDY -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-4xl">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-8">My Experience: Contractor Website That Started Winning Bids</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-amber-600 pl-6 py-5 bg-amber-50 rounded-r">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-amber-800 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE BEFORE</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Apex Builders, general contractor in Phoenix suburbs. 15 years in business. Quality craftsmanship, fair pricesâ€”but losing bids regularly to contractors with worse work. Website was outdated: generic template with 6 stock photos (not even real projects). No project galleries. No before/after photos. "Contact for quote" form with no pricing info. License number buried in footer. No service area map. Homeowner searching for kitchen remodel contractor: visits 5 contractor websites. Apex site looked like a fly-by-night operation compared to competitors with real project photos, transparent pricing, "Licensed & Insured" prominently displayed. Owner Marcus Chen was frustrated: "We do better work than half the guys getting hired, but homeowners never give us a chance. They look at our website and move on." He was watching inferior contractors win projects while Apex sat idle.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-amber-600 pl-6 py-5 bg-amber-50 rounded-r">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-amber-800 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE FIX</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">January 2024. Marcus rebuilt on Squarespace. Created project galleries organized by type: kitchens, bathrooms, additions, outdoor living. Each project: 15-20 photos showing transformation (before/during/after), project description, timeline, cost range. Added prominent "Licensed | Bonded | Insured | License #ABC123456" section at top with trust badges. Added transparent project costs: "Kitchen Remodel $25K-50K" "Bathroom $12K-25K" "Home Addition $75K-150K." Added interactive Google Map showing exact service radius (30 miles from Phoenix). Added process timeline for each project type. Integrated Google Reviews (43 reviews, 4.8 average). Added "Get Free Quote" form prominently on every page. Mobile-optimized all galleries. Total investment: $3,500 (Squarespace subscription $23/month Ã— 12 months + $2,500 freelance copywriter + project photographer). Site launched January 15, 2024.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-amber-600 pl-6 py-5 bg-amber-50 rounded-r">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-amber-800 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE AFTER</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Results in 8 months (Januaryâ€“August 2024): <strong>Bid requests increased 312%</strong> (from 22/month to 91/month). <strong>Bid acceptance rate increased 65%</strong> (from 23% to 38% = more revenue from same leads). <strong>Qualified leads increased 189%</strong> (pricing transparency filtered tire-kickers). <strong>Average project value increased 27%</strong> (from $35K to $44Kâ€”transparent costs positioned Apex as premium, not bargain). <strong>Mobile conversion increased 71%</strong> (71% of traffic from phones, optimized galleries captured requests). Marcus raised labor rates 10% in May (no pushbackâ€”website justified premium). 79% of new clients mentioned "your project photos" or "reviews" as reason they chose Apex. One client: "I looked at 10 contractor websites. Yours was the only one that showed me actual projects you did, what it would cost, and that you're legit. Others felt sketchy."</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-amber-600 pl-6 py-5 bg-amber-50 rounded-r">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-amber-800 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE 8-MONTH BREAKDOWN</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>January (launch):</strong> 31 bid requests (vs. 22 previous January = 41% increase). 9 bids accepted (29% acceptance vs. 23% before). Licensing prominent + project photos = immediate trust boost. <strong>February-April:</strong> Word spread through homeowner referrals. February: 47 requests, 14 accepted (30%). March: 58 requests, 19 accepted (33%). April: 64 requests, 22 accepted (34%). Added more project photos to galleries. Process timeline reduced "how long" questions 73%. Sales calls shifted from explaining basics to discussing details. Closing time dropped from 4 weeks to 2 weeks. <strong>May-August:</strong> Raised labor rates 10% in May (justified by premium website, strong reviews). No pushback. May: 71 requests, 24 accepted (34%). June: 82 requests, 28 accepted (34%). July: 89 requests, 31 accepted (35%). August: 91 requests, 35 accepted (38%). Added video walkthroughs of recent projects. Google reviews jumped from 43 to 67. 8-month total revenue: $1.27M (vs. $712K previous 8 months = 78% increase). ROI: 13,314x first year ($558K revenue increase / $3,500 investment Ã— 1.5 = 159x return, annualized). Project photos + licensing + pricing = winning bids.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- THE HARD TRUTH -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-4xl">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">THE HARD TRUTH</h2>
